Do you want to play this fun word game with me? After you watch the video, come up with your own word and put it in the comments! It’s addicting!

This word building activity will engage all your students while teaching prefixes, suffixes, spelling patterns, and new vocabulary! You can use this as a center or partner work, enrichment homework, whole or small group instruction, or even a five minute filler! If the link in my profile doesn’t work because it’s a video, message me for the link to this resource.  bit.ly/expandaword

You know there’s ALWAYS a fire drill the first week of school, plan your Book Tasting accordingly! 😂🤣😂

Get your students excited about reading the first week of school!! Introduce your students to new books with an engaging and memorable experience! Photos show book tastings in groups and at individual desks. 

I used genre bookmarks for individual student books because they weren’t sitting together at genre tables. This still exposed my students to a variety of new books and genres and they had these bookmarks at their fingertips to reference. When I rang the bell, they rotated books at their own desk because they couldn’t switch tables or books. 

Students shared their favorites with the class. After they selected the books they wanted to read, I put the unwanted books in a tub for the weekend. 

We ended our Book Tasting celebration with some cupcakes and juice!

I cut tablecloths from Dollar Tree into fourths so each student can have their own decor. 

My goal is to get books in my readers’ hands the first week of school! 🙌

Link to resource in profile. bit.ly/booktastingevent @teacherspayteachers @dollartreeclassrooms #bookpusher #booklover #readersgonnaread

I love this organization for my theme board book covers! I changed over to this last year and I love it! I used to use an accordion file organizer, but it just wasn’t big enough to hold all the books anymore. I got the 4x6 container from Dollar Tree and ordered the poly dividers from Amazon.

Summer is a great time to make these book covers. If you have access to your classroom, you can take pictures of your books (spines, if they’re hardcover) and then Google the images to create them.
**Video tutorial to make the book covers coming tomorrow! 
Stay tuned…

We use this resource with every shared read aloud. My students share what they think the theme is and justify their thinking with evidence from the text. After several students share, we vote as a class, whichever theme gets the most votes is where the book is placed.

node.text: I did it!! And I loved it!! When @heyhopeking and @heywadeking asked me to present @getyourteachon I knew it was an amazing opportunity, but it was also terrifying! The minute I started presenting I felt I was in my element! These amazing educators and fellow presenters hyped me up so much! Such an incredible experience and my heart is full! To be surrounded by so many excited teachers is a dream! I reunited with friends, made new friends, and made great connections. We’re all in this together and I couldn’t be prouder to be part of such a loving and supportive community! ❤️❤️❤️

Still one of my favorite bulletin boards! Students and teachers both have 180 opportunities each school year, so make every moment matter! This was my welcome back bulletin board outside our classroom. I wanted it displayed for Meet the Teacher and I wanted my students to know together we are going to take every opportunity to change the world!

Link to bulletin board in my profile bit.ly/180schooldays

**If you need a different amount of days for your school year, you can email me after purchasing. #backtoschool #bulletinboards #makeeverydaycount #togetherwecanmakeadifference

Are you a READER on board? I love advertising reading! Along with any babies on board, there may be mathematicians, artists, honor roll students, and kindness spreaders!! These student recognition car tags are a smaller version of the lawn signs! 🙌

My readers eat these tags up!! You can have them earn one for finishing a book, reading a certain number of pages, exploring a new genre, completing a book talk, so many possibilities! 

Print, laminate, hole punch-fun and creative way to recognize students! PLUS... parents love driving around and bragging about their kid! 💗
Editable template included. Link to resource in profile. bit.ly/recognitioncartag #studentawards

node.text: It is such an honor and privilege to be invited to such a monumental event in my students’ lives. I had this beautiful young lady in my class 21 years ago! It was my first looping class to fifth grade! She lives in the area so we’ve remained in touch. I fully expect to be her child’s teacher so I felt this onesie was appropriate to make! 😂 ❤️ #relationshipsfirst
